JOHANNESBURG - Police suspect a deadly shooting on the M1 in Johannesburg, near the Glenhove road offramp on Wednesday night is a hit. One person was shot eight times and died at the scene. READ:Â Crime, fraud and collusion in South Africa A witness said three men came out of nowhere, went straight to the victim's car which was at a near-standstill in traffic, and started shooting into the vehicle. Meanwhile, Eyewitness News reports that the shooting may be linked to a Hawala money exchange scheme operating out of the Oriental Plaza. However, police could not confirm whether the shooting was connected to the money exchange scheme. "I cannot confirm this. The police investigation is still continuing," said police spokesperson Mavela Masondo. eNCA